# Introducing ArkType 2.1: The first pattern matcher to bring the power of type syntax to JS
created: 2025-02-27, last updated: 2025-10-03, [Read more](https://www.reddit.com/r/typescript/comments/1izl64u/introducing_arktype_21_the_first_pattern_matcher/)

### Introducing ArkType 2.1: The first pattern matcher to bring the power of type syntax to JS
As of today, version 2.1.0 is officially released!
The standout feature in this update is the match API, which facilitates pattern matching by allowing you to specify cases with a clear type syntax.
This results in an efficient matcher that leverages set theory to bypass unmatched branches automatically.
We are thrilled to present this not only as the first syntactic matcher in JavaScript but also as the inaugural feature of ArkType that demonstrates how runtime types can extend beyond mere validation.
...
```
const = match    " number | | null v =>,
bigint: b => `${}n    object o => for ( k in) {
o[k] = toJson(o[k]);
}
return o;
},
default: "assert"
});
...
With ArkType, you create a matcher up front using type syntax, where it's parsed and optimized.
Then when you invoke it later, it's super fast with great error messages (the announcement post actually gives a comparison to ts-pattern).
